#ssh into pogoplug
#find the pogoplug ip by looking at the list of connected devices on your router
#the pogoplug MAC address us printed at the bottom of the device. compare that to find the correct ip
#the pogoplug default password is "ceadmin"

#kill all the processes running on pogoplug
#mine shows no process because i already killed them before

Pogoplug:~$ killall hbwd
killall: hbwd: no process killed

#download the uboot loader from the jeff.doozan site

Pogoplug:~$ cd /tmp

Pogoplug:/tmp$ ls -l
-rw-r--r--    1 root     root           29 Jan  1 00:00 resolv.conf
drwxr-xr-x    2 root     root           60 Jan  1 00:00 var

Pogoplug:/tmp$ wget http://jeff.doozan.com/debian/uboot/install_uboot_mtd0.sh
Connecting to jeff.doozan.com (50.116.34.13:80)
install_uboot_mtd0.s 100% |*******************************| 18406  --:--:-- ETA

#set the right permissions
Pogoplug:/tmp$ chmod +x install_uboot_mtd0.sh

#install the uboot loader now...
Pogoplug:/tmp$ ./install_uboot_mtd0.sh

!!!!!!  DANGER DANGER DANGER DANGER DANGER DANGER  !!!!!!

If you lose power to your device while running this script,
it could be left in an unusable state.

This script will replace the bootloader on /dev/mtd0.

!!!!!!  DANGER DANGER DANGER DANGER DANGER DANGER  !!!!!!

If you lose power to your device while running this script,
it could be left in an unusable state.

This script will replace the bootloader on /dev/mtd0.

This installer will only work on the following devices:
 Seagate Dockstar
 Seagate GoFlex Net
 Seagate GoFlex Home
 Pogoplug v1
 Pogoplug Pink (v2)
Do not run this installer on any other device.

By typing ok, you agree to assume all liabilities and risks 
associated with running this installer.

If you agree, type 'ok' and press ENTER to continue: ok

#prepare the USB disk for ArchLinux

Pogoplug:/tmp$ wget http://archlinuxarm.org/os/pogoplug/mke2fs
Connecting to archlinuxarm.org (50.116.36.110:80)
